info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Compute the FWI fire danger index. Input measure is expected to follow the format:
- the time series is expressed in days;
- for each day there must be a group of 4 ordered values: accumulated rainfall of 24 hours,temperature at noon (Â°C),relative humidity at noon (%),wind speed at noon (km h-1);
- all inputs must be of the same oph_type.
For each input measure there will always be a 4-value output (ffmc,dmc,dc and the chosen index).

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure : input measures.
- date : date of the first day useful to compute daylight hours according to format dd/mm/yyyy for all other days (date+1,date+2...).
- lat : latitude useful to compute daylight hours for all measures.
- index : name of the requested index.
					'FFMC' : Fine Fuel Moisture Code;
					'DMC' : Duff Moisture Code;
					'DC' : Drought Code;
					'ISI' : Initial Spread Index;
					'BUI' : Build Up Index;
					'DSR' : Daily Severity Rating;
					'FWI' : Fire Weather Index (default).
- prev_ffmc : FFMC value at day 0 (default is 0).
- prev_dmc : DMC value at day 0 (default is 0).
- prev_dc : DC value at day 0 (default is 0).

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
Compute the FWI index from oph_doubles for days starting from 01/01/2014 with a latitude of 40.5 degrees.
oph_fdi_fwi('OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',measure,'01/01/2014',40.5)
